definitions.definition: Any of several trees , of the genus Jacaranda , native to tropical South America , that have pale purple, funnel-shaped flowers. In horticultural use refers specifically to Jacaranda mimosifolia .
The hard, dark wood of these trees.
A trade name for similar hardwood timber from certain species of Dalbergia , notably Dalbergia frutescens , Dalbergia nigra and Dalbergia refusa .
